premise_source_doc_sentence: The Union Army was the land force that fought for the Union during the American Civil War , 1861 to 1865 .
It included the permanent regular army of the United States , which was augmented by massive numbers of temporary units consisting of volunteers as well as conscripts .
The Union Army fought and eventually defeated the Confederate Army during the war .
At least two and a half million men served in the Union Army ; almost all were volunteers .
About 360,000 Union soldiers died from all causes ; 280,000 were wounded and 200,000 deserted .
Over 21,000 recruits are trained each year .
